    <abstract>
      <t>Computing in the Network (COIN) has the potential to enable a wide variety of use cases. The diversity in use cases makes general considerations challenging. In an effort to capture the breadth of possible scenarios, another COINRG document presents a selection of concrete use cases, each representing a broader set of settings. This document analyzes the described use cases (and potentially further settings) to identify general aspects of interest across all use cases to steer future COIN discussions.</t>
    </abstract>
